body:
sorry this is not an iusse but wanna know how to decode an GIF into PNG sequences.
I use the code below but it does not seem to work:

    using (var codec = SKCodec.Create(stream))
            {
                var info = codec.Info;
                stream.Position = 0;
                for (int i = 0; i < codec.FrameCount; i++) 
                {
                    var skbitmap = new SKBitmap(info.Width, info.Height, true);
                    IntPtr length;
                    var result = codec.GetPixels(skbitmap.Info, skbitmap.GetPixels(out length));
                    if (result == SKCodecResult.Success)
                    {
                        resizeAndSaveImage(tempDir + "/" + i + ".png", skbitmap, srcRect, dstRect, SKEncodedImageFormat.Png);
                        stream.Position += skbitmap.ByteCount;    //move to next frame??????
                    }
                    else
                        throw new InvalidDataException();
                }
            }


problems:
1, `codec.FrameCount` seems always 1 but not the correct gif frame count
2, `codec.GetPixels` returns `SKCodecResult.IncompleteInput` I have no idea what does it mean.
3, what is the right way to decode GIF?

Thanks in advance.
